## CLI Tools (Excluding my own)

I have notes on hundreds of CLI tools so this is far from an exhaustive list.

- [Asciicinema: Record a terminal](https://asciinema.org/)
- [Bashtop: Process-Manager](https://github.com/aristocratos/bashtop)
- [Catimg: Print an image to a terminal](https://github.com/posva/catimg)
- [Column: Columnate lists and convert to JSON](https://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man1/column.1.html)
- [Dog: DNS client](https://github.com/ogham/dog)
- [Dstat: monitor system resources](https://linux.die.net/man/1/dstat)
- [Entr: Rerun a command on file-change](https://github.com/clibs/entr)
- [Fdfind: User-friendly find](https://github.com/sharkdp/fd)
- [Fzf: Interactive fuzzy-find](https://github.com/junegunn/fzf)
- [Gron: Flatten JSON to a property-list](https://github.com/tomnomnom/gron)
- [HTTPie: CLI HTTP Client](https://httpie.io/)
- [Jo: Construct JSON](https://github.com/jpmens/jo)
- [JQ: Manipulate JSON](https://stedolan.github.io/jq/)
- [Neofetch](https://github.com/dylanaraps/neofetch)
- [Strace: monitor syscalls](https://strace.io/)
- [Upower: monitor power supplies](https://upower.freedesktop.org/)
- [Yadm: Dotfile manager](https://yadm.io/)

